<item>
            <title>[MATH-657] Division by zero</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-657</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In class &lt;tt&gt;Complex&lt;/tt&gt;, division by zero always returns NaN. I think that it should return NaN only when the numerator is also &lt;tt&gt;ZERO&lt;/tt&gt;, otherwise the result should be &lt;tt&gt;INF&lt;/tt&gt;. See &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riemann_sphere#Arithmetic_operations&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12521240">MATH-657</key>
            <summary>Division by zero</summary>
